# âœ… Column-by-Column Explanation

## ğŸ•’ Time Features

These create cyclical representations of time so ML models can learn periodic patterns.

- 1. UtcTime

Unix timestamp

- 2. LocalDate

Human-readable date for Kiev (YYYY-MM-DD).

- 3. LocalHour

Hour of day (0â€“23) in local time.

# âœ… â³ Cyclical Time Encodings

These are sine/cosine transforms so ML can understand cyclic behavior (day, week, month, year).

Why?
Because hour 23 and hour 0 are far apart numerically, but adjacent cyclically.

- 4â€“5. SineDay, CosineDay

Encode hour of day (0â€“23) on a circle.

Helps model daily temperature/pollution cycles.

- 6â€“7. SineWeek, CosineWeek

Day of the week (Monâ€¦Sun) encoded cyclically.

- 8â€“9. SineMonth, CosineMonth

Month of year encoded cyclically (Jan â†’ Dec).

- 10â€“11. SineYear, CosineYear

Encodes long-term yearly seasonality.

# ğŸŒ¡ Weather Features

